on an island in Sebago Lake.

Getting to Frye Island is easy.  The island is accessible via a public car ferry that runs every half hour from Raymond, Maine's Cape Road.  Two Ferry's, the Leisure Lady and the Ellie Corliss, each have a 9 car capacity, and take only 10 minutes to make the short trip to the island.

Frye Island has a network of roads that span the entire island.  All roads are dirt/gravel, and are maintained extremly well by the public works department.
Transportation on the island is mainly car or golf cart (most homeowners own golf carts which are permissable as transportation on the island).
There are also numerous bike / hiking trails on the island for those looking for outdoor adventures.
